{"name":"Mathlib.RingTheory.Coprime.Ideal","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.DFinsupp","Mathlib.RingTheory.Ideal.Operations"],"declarations":[{"info":{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/8c661e5492d1852ac9a417cfc675b6545d77c4b7/Mathlib/RingTheory/Coprime/Ideal.lean#L31-L112","name":"Ideal.iSup_iInf_eq_top_iff_pairwise","line":31,"kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Coprime/Ideal.html#Ideal.iSup_iInf_eq_top_iff_pairwise","doc":"A finite family of ideals is pairwise coprime (that is, any two of them generate the whole ring)\niff when taking all the possible intersections of all but one of these ideals, the resulting family\nof ideals still generate the whole ring.\n\nFor example with three ideals : `I ⊔ J = I ⊔ K = J ⊔ K = ⊤ ↔ (I ⊓ J) ⊔ (I ⊓ K) ⊔ (J ⊓ K) = ⊤`.\n\nWhen ideals are all of the form `I i = R ∙ s i`, this is equivalent to the\n`exists_sum_eq_one_iff_pairwise_coprime` lemma."},"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/RingTheory/Coprime/Ideal.html#Ideal.iSup_iInf_eq_top_iff_pairwise\"><span class=\"name\">Ideal</span>.<span class=\"name\">iSup_iInf_eq_top_iff_pairwise</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{ι : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{R : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_2}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Ring/Defs.html#CommSemiring\">CommSemiring</a> <span class=\"fn\">R</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{t : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Finset/Basic.html#Finset\">Finset</a> <span class=\"fn\">ι</span></spa